Title: MS 27 folio 1
Description.abstract: 1. f. 1-5: [Prime] Ad primam hymnus. Iam lucis orto sidere etc. Ps. [53], Deus in nomine tuo salvum me fac et in vritute tua iudica me ... Ps. [118], Beati immaculati in via qui ambulant in lege domini ... [f. 3, Athanasian Creed] Simbolum. Quicumque vult salvus esse ante omnia opus est ut teneat catholicam fidem.Hymn for Prime, attr. to Ambrose, followed by Ps. 53. Then follows Ps. 118.1-32, with 2-line initials at verses 1, 9, 17, and 25. Because of its length, Ps. 118 is divided into four parts for Prime, Terce, Sext, and None.

Title: MS 27 folio 5
Description.abstract: 2. ff. 5-8: [Terce] Ad terciam hymnus. Nunc sancte nobis spiritus unum patri cum filio dignare promptus ingeri nostro refusus pectori ... [f. 5v] Ps. [118.33-80]. Legem pone mihi domine viam iustificationum.Hymn for Terce, attr. to Ambrose, followed by second quarter of Ps. 118, with 2-line initials at vv. 33, 49, 65.

Title: MS 27 folio 8
Description.abstract: 3. ff. 8-10v: [Sext] Ad vi^m hymnus. Rector potens verax deus qui temperas rerum vices splendore mane instruis et ignibus ...Ps. [118.81-128] Deficit in salutare tuum anima mea...Hymn for Sext, attr. to Ambrose, with last verse heavily truncated. Third quarter of Ps. 118, with 2-line initials at vv. 81, 97, 113.

Title: MS 27 folio 10
Description.abstract: 4. ff. 10v-13: [None] Ad ix^m hymnus. Rerum deus tenax vigor immotus in te permanens lucis divine tempora suscessibus determinans ... Ps. [118.129-176] Mirabilia testimonia tua ideo scrutata est ea anima mea ... quia mandata tua non sum oblitus.Hymn for None, attr. to Ambrose, with last verse heavily truncated. End of Ps. 118, with 2-line initials at vv. 129, 145, and 161. Last two words, "sum oblitus", added below bottom line.

Title: MS 27 folio 13
Description.abstract: 5. ff. 13v-16v: [Office for Good Friday] Officium de quinque vulneribus domini rostri Yesu Christi. [antiphon] Humiliavit semetipsum dominus noster Yesus Christus usque ad mortem ... Oratio. Domine Yesus Christe fili dei vivi... Lectio Zacharie prophete xii^0 capitulo. Hec die domino deus. Effundam super domum David ... [f. 14v] Secundum Johannem. In illo tempore. Sciens Yesus quod iam omnia consumata sunt... [f. 15] Secreta. Domine Ihesu Christe qui pro redemptione ... Pro omnes oratio ... Pro morbo... Pro pluviam oratio... Pro serenitatem oratio... Pro benefactoribus oratio... perpetuum rorem tue be[nedictiones] infunde. Pretende. Fidelium. [remainder of f. 16v blank]Readings from the Stations of the Cross (from 1st, 2nd, 3rd, 10th, and 11th stations; ed. Coeleste Palmetum, 1741) and the Hours of the Passion.
